</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-TEXAS-IOWA-STATE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WALKER'S PRESENCE FELT AS WILLIAMS' 350 YARDS, 5 TDS POWER
LONGHORNS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN _ While the eyes of Texas were once again upon the
Longhorns' Heisman hopeful Ricky Williams, he felt the gaze of only
two.
</P>
<P>
   Williams said he felt as if his friend and Texas football
legend, Doak Walker, was glancing down on him. Walker, 71, died
last Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``A couple of times,'' Williams said of feeling Walker's
presence.
</P>
<P>
   Williams honored his friend with a performance befitting the SMU
legend. Williams had 350 yards rushing and five touchdowns in
Texas' 54-33 Big 12 victory against Iowa State last night at
Royal-Memorial Stadium. Texas is 3-2, overall and 0-2 in the Big 12
and Iowa State is 2-3, 0-2.
</P>
<P>
   Williams introduced himself to Walker while in Dallas in January
to a accept the Doak Walker Award for college football's top
running back.
</P>
<P>
   A friendship quickly developed.
</P>
<P>
   Walker was paralyzed in a skiing accident 10 days later,
touching Williams in a way he hardly imagined. Then came Walker's
death.
</P>
<P>
   Williams sent a message of condolence to Walker's family. He
displayed Walker's No. 37 on his helmet. His biggest tribute,
though, came with his performance.
</P>
<P>
   He scored his fifth and final touchdown of the night, his 20th
this season and his 67th of his Texas career with 6 minutes, 37
seconds remaining in the fourth quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was a really tough week for Ricky. We could see it in
practice,'' Longhorns linebacker Dusty Renfro said. ``There was a
lot going on and he overcame it all. We've almost come to expect
that from him.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams' 350-yard performance established a Longhorns mark, and
also began a full-fledged assault on NCAA all-times lists.
</P>
<P>
   In a single game, he jumped to No. 1 in touchdowns (67) and
rushing touchdowns (65). He also jumped six players to take over
the No. 4 spot on the NCAA all-time rushing list with 5,241 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Only Tony Dorsett (6,082), Charles White (5,598) and Herschel
Walker (5,259) have more.
</P>
<P>
   ``If he's not the best player in the country, he's definitely
one of them,'' said Texas coach Mack Brown said, resuming Williams'
Heisman campaign in earnest. ``He's a tremendous competitor and a
tremendous athlete.''
</P>
<P>
   And with everybody's eyes on Williams _ including Iowa State's _
UT's passing game had a field day, too.
</P>
<P>
   Longhorns quarterback Major Applewhite went 3-for-3 for 71 yards
on Texas' opening drive, including a 9-yard touchdown pass to Derek
Lewis.
</P>
<P>
   Applewhite finished 15-for-26 for 248 yards and two touchdowns.
Kwame Cavil and Derek Lewis were Applewhite's main targets, gaining
102 and 60 yards, respectively.
</P>
<P>
   Texas' much-maligned defense, ranking 99th among 112 Division
I-A defenses, held Cyclones tailback Darren Davis to 53 yards on 20
attempts.
</P>
<P>
   Stopping Todd Bandhauer-to-Damien Groce proved to be another
deal altogether.
</P>
<P>
   Bandhauer finished with an Iowa State-record 437 yards passing
and five touchdowns while Groce had 10 receptions for 137 yards and
two touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   Texas responded to that inadequacy by simply scoring more _ a
Williams-led endeavor.
</P>
<P>
   He has generated bigger numbers and gaudier performances in his
time.
</P>
<P>
   He displayed his most emotional against Iowa State, a player
remembering a player and a friend in a way only players appreciate.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's been a hard week,'' Williams said, school, a bit of
soreness and Walker keeping him up late into Friday night. ``He was
in my heart the whole game.''
High marks Highlights of Ricky Williams' record night:
</P>
<P>
   Set a UT single-game rushing record of 350 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Set the NCAA career record for touchdowns with 67 and rushing
touchdowns with 65.
</P>
<P>
   Set the NCAA career record (404) for most points by a
non-kicker.
</P>
<P>
   Jumped to fourth place on the NCAA career rushing list with
5,241 yards, past Archie Griffin of Ohio State, who had 5,177
yards.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
