   6. UNDER THE TUSCAN SUN, by Frances Mayes.
</P>
<P>
   (Broadway, $13.) A celebration of life in the
</P>
<P>
   Italian countryside by an American poet.
</P>
<P>
   7. ANATOMY OF THE SPIRIT, by Caroline Myss. (Three Rivers,
</P>
<P>
   $14.) Holistic medicine. (b).
</P>
<P>
   8. CITIZEN SOLDIERS, by Stephen E. Ambrose. (Touchstone/S&AMP;S,
</P>
<P>
   $16.) The U.S. Army from Normandy to Germany's
</P>
<P>
   surrender.
</P>
<P>
   9 . A CHILD CALLED ``IT,'' by Dave Pelzer.
</P>
<P>
   (Health Communications, $9.95.) The autobiography
</P>
<P>
   of a man who survived his mother's abuse.
</P>
<P>
   10.(x) D-DAY, June 6, 1944, by Stephen E. Ambrose.
</P>
<P>
   (Touchstone/S&AMP;S, $16.) An account of the Allied invasion
</P>
<P>
   of Normandy.
</P>
<P>
   11.(x) THE COLOR OF WATER, by James McBride. (Riverhead, $12.)
</P>
<P>
   A black writer and musician recalls his experiences growing
</P>
<P>
   up with his white mother in a Brooklyn, N.Y., housing project.
</P>
<P>
   12.(x) INTO THE WILD, by Jon Krakauer. (Anchor/Doubleday,
$12.95.)
</P>
<P>
   The story of a young man whose obsession
</P>
<P>
   with the wilderness had a tragic end in Alaska.
</P>
<P>
