<P>
   BANKING-POLITICS (Washington) _ After years of edging to the
brink of passage, legislation to modernize the nation's banking and
financial services industries has hit yet another political snag:
the D'Amato-Schumer Senate race, in which the White House has
indicated its willingness to veto a bill the administration would
normally support. The Democrats do not want to let the Republican
Al D'Amato go into the November election being able to tout his
success as a sponsor of the banking legislation.
</P>
<P>
   VIACOM-BLOCKBUSTER (Undated) _ Ever since Viacom acquired
Blockbuster in hopes of gaining the cash flow that would help
Viacom pay for Paramount, Blockbuster has instead been a drag on an
otherwise robust business. But finally, Sumner Redstone thinks he
has come up with a boffo plan for Blockbuster. By Geraldine
Fabrikant.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-BANKING (Undated) _ A look at some new developments in
electronic banking. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   HITECH-TEMPS (Undated) _ International Network Solutions, a temp
agency for high-powered network engineers, is one of the most
important companies nobody has ever heard of. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   SEC-Y2K-REPORTS (Undated) _ For the first time, companies'
quarterly reports to the SEC must contain an indication of the
financial impact of dealing with their Year 2000 computing
problems. By Barnaby J. Feder.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-DOMAIN (Washington) _ The latest on the
private-industry plan to take over administration of Internet
domain names.
</P>
<P>
