<SLUG> BC-EQUITIES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EQUITIES 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   These equity and convertible debt offerings are expected this
week:
</P>
<P>
   Computer Literacy Inc., Sunnyvale, Calif., an initial public
offering of 3 million shares. NMS.
</P>
<P>
   Dycom Industries Inc., Palm Beach Gardens, Fla., 3 million
shares. NMS.
</P>
<P>
   Ixos Software Aktiengesellschaft, Munich, Germany, an initial
public offering of $3 million American depository shares, each
representing one-fifth of one ordinary share, 1.5 in the U.S. and
Canada. Goldman, Sachs &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Lincoln Heritage Corp., Austin, Texas, an initial public
offering of 1 million shares. Tejas Securities.
</P>
<P>
   Orthopaedic Biosystems Ltd. Inc., Scottsdale, Ariz., an initial
public offering of 2 million shares. Cruttenden Roth Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Performance Printing Corp., Dallas, an initial public offering
of 1.2 million units, consisting of one common share and one
warrant. First London.
</P>
<P>
   Swisscom AG, Bern, Switzerland, an initial public offering of
22.1 million shares, 4.4 million in the U.S. and Canada. Warburg,
Dillon Read &AMP; Co.
</P>
<P>
   Univision Communications Inc., Los Angeles, 11.5 million shares,
10.4 million in the U.S. and Canada. Morgan Stanley Dean Witter.
</P>
<P>
   Source: MCM Corporatewatch.
