   &UR; Alexander McQueen &LR; , the British fashion designer known for his
avant-garde clothing, his tough-guy attitude and his foul language,
broke into tears last week while defending his use of model  &UR; Aimee
Mullins &LR; . Mullins, who was born with a birth defect that resulted
in the amputation of her legs, wears prosthetics.
</P>
<P>
   Her strut on the catwalk last week caused Yves Saint Laurent
president  &UR; Pierre Berge &LR;  to call McQueen a ``voyeur-provocateur.''
</P>
<P>
