<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-04 22:20 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A8905 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-FALCONS-SIDE-COX     10-04 0490
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-SIDE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Do the Falcons make the grade?
 &HT;    By Jeff Schultz
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   OFFENSE
</P>
<P>
   PASSING GAME: B
</P>
<P>
   Quarterback Chris Chandler had touchdown passes of 30 yards to
Tony Martin and 26 to seldom-used tight end O.J. Santiago, as well
as key long gainers to Jamal Anderson (27 on a screen) and Terance
Mathis (38 on play action). He also had his first career reception,
catching a 22-yarder on a halfback option from Tim Dwight. The
downside was two interceptions (Rod Smith and Greg Lloyd) and a
near third pickoff that was dropped by Smith. Pass protection gets
high marks, as Carolina was limited to one sack.
</P>
<P>
   RUNNING GAME: A
</P>
<P>
   Jamal Anderson rushed for more than 100 yards (117 on 31
attempts) in consecutive weeks for the first time in his career.
The long runs of 20 yards came early (Atlanta's first offensive
possession, a touchdown drive) and late (a 20-yard touchdown on a
draw play). The effectiveness of the running game early made
Carolina more tentative with its blitz. The line blocked well,
particularly between the tackles.
</P>
<P>
   RETURN GAME: A-MINUS
</P>
<P>
   Rookie Tim Dwight, a fourth-round pick, has been one of the
great finds in the draft. He returned the opening kickoff 93 yards
for a touchdown and averaged 25.3 yards on his other three
runbacks. The only blunder on a return came in the second quarter,
when Devin Bush, playing in his first game of the year, was ejected
for cheap-shotting Leonard Wheeler after the whistle on a punt
return. Morten Andersen made all three of his field goal attempts
(23, 25, 28).
</P>
<P>
   DEFENSE
</P>
<P>
   VS. THE PASS: C
</P>
<P>
   Granted, many of the Panthers' yards came when the game was out
of reach. But the Falcons' secondary took some hits, as Kerry
Collins threw for 302 yards and three touchdowns. Big plays
included Raghib Ismail beating Ray Buchanan (46 yards), Wesley
Walls beating Jessie Tuggle (24-yard touchdown) and Muhsin Muhammad
beating Ronnie Bradford (72-yard touchdown). On the plus side,
Buchanan had an interception at the goal line when the Falcons led
14-3. William White had three big plays in the second half _ an
18-yard fumble return for a TD (Muhammad dropped the ball after a
reception), an interception with a 36-yard return and a forced
fumble against tight end Luther Broughton that Ronnie Bradford
recovered.
</P>
<P>
   VS. THE RUN: B-MINUS
</P>
<P>
   Carolina's Fred Lane ran the ball well early, but the Panthers
had to abandon the running game when the score became lopsided. The
Falcons also had two dumb penalties on running plays _ a face mask
by Eugene Robinson and an unnecessary roughness by Lester
Archambeau.
</P>
<P>
   COVERAGE GAME: A
</P>
<P>
   Carolina did not have a significant kickoff return all game and
did not bring back a punt against Dan Stryzinski. Travis Hall
blocked his second PAT attempt of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
