<P>
   FIRST HALF ROUNDUP
</P>
<P>
   FIRST QUARTER: The Falcons took advantage of Carolina's special
teams miscues to bolt to a 14-0 lead less than 6:30 into the
quarter. WR Tim Dwight returned the opening kickoff 93 yards for a
score. After Panthers PK John Kasay missed a 54-yard field goal,
Atlanta drove 56 yards on five plays, scoring when WR Tony Martin
beat FS Brent Alexander on a deep post to take a 30-yard touchdown
pass from QB Chris Chandler. Score: Falcons 14, Carolina 3.
</P>
<P>
   SECOND QUARTER: Carolina continued to miss opportunities to get
back into the game. The Panthers failed to recover a fumble at the
Atlanta 13-yard line after LB Kevin Greene overwhelmed a
double-team block by OT Ephraim Salaam and FB Gary Downs. A few
minutes later, QB Kerry Collins underthrew TE Wesley Walls in the
end zone, and Falcons CB Ray Buchanan intercepted. A field goal by
PK Morten Andersen was set up when Dwight completed a throw-back
pass to Chandler for 22 yards. Score: Falcons 17, Carolina 3.
</P>
