<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Atlanta, Dallas top picks for weekend football
 &HT;    By Len Pasquarelli
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Last week: Packers 37, Panthers 30; 49ers 31, Falcons 20.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Panthers lead 4-3.
</P>
<P>
   Notable: Five of seven games, including Atlanta's 19-14 victory
Sept. 6, have been decided by six points or fewer. ... Carolina has
held the Falcons to an average 69.7 rushing yards in last three
meetings. ... Falcons RB Jamal Anderson is on pace for a
career-best 1,520 yards. ... Atlanta defense hasn't allowed a
100-yard rusher in 11 games. ... The Panthers sacked QB Chris
Chandler six times in the opener, including three by LB Kevin
Greene.
</P>
<P>
   Favorite: Atlanta by 3.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys
</P>
<P>
   at Redskins
</P>
<P>
   1:01 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Last week: Raiders 13, Cowboys 12; Broncos 38, Redskins 16.
</P>
<P>
   Series: Cowboys lead 41-31-2.
</P>
